==English==
===Etymology===
From ecclesiastical Latin [[haeresiarcha]], from ecclesiastical Greek [[ἁιρεσιαρχης]] ‘leader of a sect’, corresponding to [[heresy]] + [[-arch]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/hɛˈri:zɪɑ:k/}} (''UK'')

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#The founder of a [[heresy]], or a major ecclesiastical proponent of such a heresy.

